{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Charles and Ray were a team. They were husband and wife."},{"time":3000,"text":"Despite the New York Times' and Vanity Fair's best efforts recently,"},{"time":6000,"text":"they're not brothers. (Laughter)"},{"time":8000,"text":"And they were a lot of fun."},{"time":10000,"text":"You know, Ray was the one who wore the ampersands in the family."},{"time":12000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15000,"text":"We are going to focus on Charles today, because it is Charles' 100th birthday."},{"time":18000,"text":"But when I speak of him, I'm really speaking of both of them as a team."},{"time":21000,"text":"Here's Charles when he was three. So he would be 100 this June."},{"time":24000,"text":"We have a lot of cool celebrations that we're going to do."},{"time":26000,"text":"The thing about their work"},{"time":28000,"text":"is that most people come to the door of furniture --"},{"time":30000,"text":"I suspect you probably recognize this chair"},{"time":32000,"text":"and some of the others I'm going to show you."},{"time":34000,"text":"But we're going to first enter through the door of the Big Top."},{"time":57000,"text":"The whole thing about this, though, is that, you know, why am I showing it?"},{"time":59000,"text":"Is it because Charles and Ray made this film?"},{"time":61000,"text":"This is actually a training film for a clown college that they had."},{"time":65000,"text":"They also practiced a clown act when the future of furniture"},{"time":68000,"text":"was not nearly as auspicious as it turned out to be."},{"time":71000,"text":"There is a picture of Charles. So let's watch the next clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"The film that we're about to see is a film they made for the Moscow World's Fair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"Video: This is the land."},{"time":81000,"text":"It has many contrasts."},{"time":83000,"text":"It is rough and it is flat."},{"time":87000,"text":"In places it is cold."},{"time":89000,"text":"In some it is hot."},{"time":106000,"text":"Too much rain falls on some areas,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and not enough on others."},{"time":113000,"text":"But people live on this land."},{"time":116000,"text":"And, as in Russia,"},{"time":118000,"text":"they are drawn together into towns and cities."},{"time":122000,"text":"Here is something of the way they live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"Eames Demetrios: Now, this is a film that was hardly ever seen in the United States."},{"time":128000,"text":"It was on seven screens and it was 200 feet across."},{"time":132000,"text":"And it was at the height of the Cold War."},{"time":134000,"text":"The Nixon-Khrushchev Kitchen Debate"},{"time":136000,"text":"happened about 50 feet from where this was shown."},{"time":138000,"text":"And yet, how did it start?"},{"time":140000,"text":"You know, commonality, the first line"},{"time":142000,"text":"in Charles' narration was,"},{"time":144000,"text":"\"The same stars that shine down on Russia"},{"time":146000,"text":"shine down on the United States. From the sky,"},{"time":148000,"text":"our cities look much the same.\""},{"time":150000,"text":"It was that human connection that Charles and Ray always found in everything."},{"time":153000,"text":"And you can imagine, and the thing about it is,"},{"time":155000,"text":"that they believed that the human mind could handle this number of images"},{"time":158000,"text":"because the important thing was to get the gestalt"},{"time":160000,"text":"of what the images were about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"So that was just a little snip."},{"time":164000,"text":"But the thing about Charles and Ray"},{"time":166000,"text":"is that they were always modeling stuff."},{"time":168000,"text":"They were always trying things out."},{"time":170000,"text":"I think one of the things I am passionate about, my grandparents work,"},{"time":172000,"text":"I'm passionate about my work,"},{"time":174000,"text":"but on top of all that I'm passionate"},{"time":177000,"text":"about a holistic vision of design,"},{"time":179000,"text":"where design is a life skill, not a professional skill."},{"time":182000,"text":"And you know, those of us with kids often want our kids to take music."},{"time":185000,"text":"I'm no exception."},{"time":187000,"text":"But it's not about them becoming Bono or Tracy Chapman."},{"time":190000,"text":"It's about getting that music thing going through their heads and their thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"Design is the same way. Design has to become that same way."},{"time":196000,"text":"And this is a model that they did of that seven-screen presentation."},{"time":198000,"text":"And Charles just checking it out there."},{"time":201000,"text":"So now we're going to go through that door of furniture."},{"time":203000,"text":"This is an unusual installation of airport seating."},{"time":205000,"text":"So what we're going to see is some of the icons of Eames furniture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"And the thing about their furniture is that they said the role of the designer"},{"time":212000,"text":"was essentially that of a good host,"},{"time":214000,"text":"anticipating the needs of the guest."},{"time":216000,"text":"So those are cool images. But these are ones I think are really cool."},{"time":218000,"text":"These are all the prototypes. These are the mistakes,"},{"time":221000,"text":"although I don't think mistakes is the right word in design."},{"time":223000,"text":"It's just the things you try out"},{"time":225000,"text":"to kind of make it work better."},{"time":227000,"text":"And you know some of them would probably be terrible chairs."},{"time":230000,"text":"Some of them are kind of cool looking. It's like \"Hey, why didn't they try that?\""},{"time":233000,"text":"It was that hands-on iterative process"},{"time":235000,"text":"which is so much like vernacular design"},{"time":238000,"text":"and folk design in traditional cultures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"And I think that's one of the commonalities between modernism"},{"time":243000,"text":"and traditional design. I think it may be a real common ground"},{"time":246000,"text":"as we kind of figure out what on earth to do in the next 20 or 30 years."},{"time":249000,"text":"The other thing that's kind of cool is that"},{"time":251000,"text":"you look at this and in the media when people say design,"},{"time":254000,"text":"they actually mean style."},{"time":256000,"text":"And I'm really here to talk about design."},{"time":258000,"text":"But you know the object is just a pivot."},{"time":260000,"text":"It's a pivot between a process and a system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"And this is a little film I made"},{"time":267000,"text":"about the making of the Eames lounge chair."},{"time":269000,"text":"The design process for Charles and Ray"},{"time":273000,"text":"never ended in manufacturing."},{"time":278000,"text":"It continued. They were always trying to make thing better and better."},{"time":280000,"text":"Because it's like as Bill Clinton was saying about Rwandan health clinics."},{"time":285000,"text":"It's not enough to create one."},{"time":287000,"text":"You've got to create a system that will work better and better."},{"time":289000,"text":"So I've always liked this prototype picture."},{"time":291000,"text":"Because it just kind of, you know, doesn't get any more basic than that."},{"time":293000,"text":"You try things out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"This is a relatively famous chair."},{"time":297000,"text":"Its early version had an \"X\" base. That's what the collectors like."},{"time":300000,"text":"Charles and Ray liked this one because it was better."},{"time":302000,"text":"It worked better: \"H\" base, much more practical."},{"time":305000,"text":"This is something called a splint."},{"time":307000,"text":"And I was very touched by Dean Kamen's"},{"time":309000,"text":"work for the military, or for the soldiers,"},{"time":313000,"text":"because Charles and Ray designed a molded plywood splint. This is it."},{"time":317000,"text":"And they'd been working on furniture before."},{"time":319000,"text":"But doing these splints they learned a lot about the manufacturing process,"},{"time":322000,"text":"which was incredibly important to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"I'm trying to show you too much,"},{"time":337000,"text":"because I want you to really get a broth of ideas and images."},{"time":339000,"text":"This is a house that Charles and Ray designed."},{"time":341000,"text":"My sister is chasing someone else. It's not me."},{"time":344000,"text":"Although I endorse heartily the fact that he stole her diary, it's not me."},{"time":348000,"text":"And then this is a film, on the lower left, that Charles and Ray made."},{"time":352000,"text":"Now look at that plastic chair."},{"time":355000,"text":"The house is 1949."},{"time":357000,"text":"The chair is done in 1949."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"Charles and Ray,"},{"time":364000,"text":"they didn't obsess about style for it's own sake."},{"time":366000,"text":"They didn't say, \"Our style is curves. Let's make the house curvy.\""},{"time":369000,"text":"They didn't say, \"Our style is grids. Let's make the chair griddy.\""},{"time":372000,"text":"They focused on the need."},{"time":374000,"text":"They tried to solve the design problem."},{"time":376000,"text":"Charles used to say, \"The extent to which you have a design style"},{"time":379000,"text":"is the extent to which you have not solved the design problem.\""},{"time":381000,"text":"It's kind of a brutal quote."},{"time":383000,"text":"This is the earlier design of that house."},{"time":385000,"text":"And again, they managed to figure out a way to make a prototype"},{"time":387000,"text":"of a house -- architecture, very expensive medium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"Here's a film we've been hearing things about."},{"time":393000,"text":"The \"Powers of Ten\" is a film they made."},{"time":396000,"text":"If we watch the next clip,"},{"time":398000,"text":"you're going to see the first version of \"Powers of Ten,\" upper left."},{"time":402000,"text":"The familiar one on the lower right."},{"time":406000,"text":"The Eames' film Tops, lower left."},{"time":409000,"text":"And a lamp that Charles designed for a church."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"Video: Which in turn belongs to a local group of galaxies."},{"time":415000,"text":"These form part of a grouping system"},{"time":417000,"text":"much as the stars do."},{"time":420000,"text":"They are so many and so varied that from this distance"},{"time":422000,"text":"they appear like the stars from Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"ED: You've seen that film, and what's so great about this"},{"time":429000,"text":"whole conference is that everybody has been talking about scale."},{"time":431000,"text":"Everybody here is coming at it from a different way."},{"time":433000,"text":"I want to give you one example."},{"time":435000,"text":"E.O. Wilson once told me that when he looked at ants --"},{"time":437000,"text":"he loved them, of course, and he wanted to learn more about them --"},{"time":440000,"text":"he consciously looked at them from the standpoint of scale."},{"time":442000,"text":"So here is the tiny creature."},{"time":444000,"text":"And yet simply by changing the frame of reference"},{"time":446000,"text":"it reveals so much, including what ended up being the TED Prize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Modeling, they tried modeling all the time. They were always modeling things."},{"time":453000,"text":"And I think part of that is that they never delegated understanding."},{"time":456000,"text":"And I think in our family we were very lucky,"},{"time":459000,"text":"because we learned about design backwards."},{"time":461000,"text":"Design was not something other."},{"time":463000,"text":"It was part of the business of life in general."},{"time":465000,"text":"It was part of the quality of life."},{"time":467000,"text":"And here is some family pictures."},{"time":470000,"text":"And you can see why I'm down on style, with a haircut like that."},{"time":472000,"text":"But anyway, (Laughter)"},{"time":474000,"text":"I remember the cut grapefruit that we would have at the Eames house when I was a kid."},{"time":477000,"text":"So we're going to watch another film."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"This is a film, the one called Toys."},{"time":482000,"text":"You can see me, I have the same haircut, in the upper right corner."},{"time":486000,"text":"Upper left is a film they did on toy trains."},{"time":490000,"text":"Lower right is a solar do-nothing toy."},{"time":493000,"text":"Lower left is Day-of-the-Dead toys."},{"time":505000,"text":"Charles used to say that toys are not as innocent as they appear."},{"time":508000,"text":"They are often the precursor to bigger things."},{"time":512000,"text":"And these ideas -- that train up there, being about the honest use of materials,"},{"time":515000,"text":"is totally the same"},{"time":517000,"text":"as the honest use of materials in the plywood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"And now I'm going to test you."},{"time":525000,"text":"This is a letter that my grandfather sent to my mom when she was five years old."},{"time":529000,"text":"So can you read it?"},{"time":531000,"text":"Lucia angel,"},{"time":533000,"text":"okay, eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"Audience: Saw many trains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"ED: Awl, also, good that the leather crafter's guild is here."},{"time":545000,"text":"Also, what is he doing? Row, rowed."},{"time":550000,"text":"Sun? No. Well is there another name for a sunrise?"},{"time":552000,"text":"Dawn, very good."},{"time":555000,"text":"Also rode on one. I ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"Audience: You had, I hope you had --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"ED: Now you've been to the website Dogs of Saint Louis"},{"time":561000,"text":"in the late, in the mid-1930's,"},{"time":563000,"text":"then you'd know that was a Great Dane."},{"time":565000,"text":"So, I hope you had a"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"Audience: Nice time, time --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"ED: Time at."},{"time":573000,"text":"Citizen Kane, rose --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"Audience: Rosebud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"ED: No, bud. \"D\"'s right. At Buddy's --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"Audience: Party. Love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"ED: Okay, good."},{"time":584000,"text":"So, \"I saw many trains and also rode on one."},{"time":586000,"text":"I hope you had a nice time at Buddy's party.\""},{"time":588000,"text":"So you guys did pretty good, cool."},{"time":591000,"text":"So my mom and Charles had this great relationship"},{"time":593000,"text":"where they'd send those sorts of things back and forth to one another."},{"time":596000,"text":"And it's all part of the, you know,"},{"time":598000,"text":"they used to say, \"Take your pleasure seriously.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"These are some images from a project of mine"},{"time":603000,"text":"that's called Kymaerica."},{"time":605000,"text":"It's sort of an alternative universe."},{"time":607000,"text":"It's kind of a reinterpretation of the landscape."},{"time":610000,"text":"Those plaques are plaques we've been installing around North America."},{"time":612000,"text":"We're about to do six in the U.K. next week."},{"time":615000,"text":"And they honor events in the linear world from the fictional world."},{"time":618000,"text":"So, of course, since it's bronze it has to be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"Video: Kymaerica with waterfalls,"},{"time":625000,"text":"tumbling through our --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627000,"text":"ED: This is one of the traditional Kymaerican songs."},{"time":629000,"text":"And so we had spelling bees in Paris, Illinois."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"Video: Your word is N. Carolina."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"Girl: Y-I-N-D-I-A-N-A."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"ED: And then Embassy Row is actually a historical site,"},{"time":643000,"text":"because in the Kymaerican story"},{"time":645000,"text":"this is where the Parisian Diaspora started, where there embassy was."},{"time":648000,"text":"So you can actually visit and have this three-dimensional"},{"time":650000,"text":"fictional experience there."},{"time":652000,"text":"And the town has really embraced it."},{"time":654000,"text":"We had the spelling bee in conjunction with the Gwomeus Club."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656000,"text":"But what is really cool is that we take our visual environment"},{"time":659000,"text":"as inevitable. And it's not."},{"time":662000,"text":"Other things could have happened. The Japanese could have discovered Monterey."},{"time":665000,"text":"And we could have been born 100,000 years ago."},{"time":667000,"text":"And there are a lot of fun things. This is the Museum of the Bench."},{"time":669000,"text":"They have trading cards"},{"time":671000,"text":"and all sorts of cool things."},{"time":673000,"text":"And you're kind of trapped in the texture of Kymaerica."},{"time":677000,"text":"The Tahatchabe, the great road building culture."},{"time":679000,"text":"A guy named Nobu Naga,"},{"time":681000,"text":"the so-called Japanese Columbus."},{"time":683000,"text":"But now I'm going to return you to the real world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"And this is Cranbrook. I've got a real treat for you,"},{"time":688000,"text":"which is the first film that Charles ever made."},{"time":690000,"text":"So let's watch that. Nobody's ever seen it."},{"time":693000,"text":"Cranbrook is very generous to let us show it for the first time here."},{"time":697000,"text":"It's a film about Maya Gretel, a famous ceramicist, and a teacher at Cranbrook."},{"time":701000,"text":"And he made it for the 1939 faculty exhibition."},{"time":705000,"text":"Silent. We don't have a track for it yet."},{"time":711000,"text":"Very simple. It's just a start. But it's that learn-by-doing thing."},{"time":714000,"text":"You want to learn how to make films? Go make a movie."},{"time":716000,"text":"And you try something out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"But here is what's really great."},{"time":720000,"text":"See that chair there? The orange one? That's the organic chair. 1940."},{"time":724000,"text":"At the same time that Charles was doing that chair,"},{"time":726000,"text":"he was doing this film."},{"time":728000,"text":"So my point is that this scope of vision, this holistic vision"},{"time":730000,"text":"of design, was with them from the beginning."},{"time":732000,"text":"It wasn't like \"Oh, we made some chairs and got successful."},{"time":734000,"text":"Now we're going to do some movies.\""},{"time":736000,"text":"It was always part of how they looked at the world. And that's what's really powerful."},{"time":739000,"text":"And I think that all of us in this room, as you move design forward,"},{"time":742000,"text":"it's not about just doing one thing."},{"time":746000,"text":"It's about how you approach problems. And there is this huge, beautiful commonality"},{"time":749000,"text":"between design, business and the world."},{"time":752000,"text":"So we're going to do the last clip."},{"time":754000,"text":"And I've shown you some of the images. I just want to focus on sound now."},{"time":756000,"text":"So this is Charles' voice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"Charles Eames: In India, those without, and the lowest in caste,"},{"time":763000,"text":"eat very often, particularly in southern India,"},{"time":765000,"text":"they eat off of a banana leaf."},{"time":768000,"text":"And those a little bit up the scale"},{"time":772000,"text":"eat off of a sort of a low-fired ceramic dish."},{"time":776000,"text":"And a little bit higher, why they have a glaze"},{"time":779000,"text":"on a thing they call a thali."},{"time":782000,"text":"If you're up the scale a little bit more,"},{"time":784000,"text":"why, a brass thali."},{"time":786000,"text":"And then things get to be a little questionable."},{"time":790000,"text":"There are things like silver-plated thalis."},{"time":793000,"text":"And there is solid silver thalis."},{"time":795000,"text":"And I suppose some nut has had a"},{"time":798000,"text":"gold thali that he's eaten off of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"But you can go beyond that."},{"time":802000,"text":"And the guys that have not only means,"},{"time":807000,"text":"but a certain amount of knowledge and understanding,"},{"time":812000,"text":"go to the next step, and they eat off a banana leaf."},{"time":817000,"text":"And I think that in these times"},{"time":821000,"text":"when we fall back and regroup,"},{"time":823000,"text":"that somehow or other,"},{"time":827000,"text":"the banana leaf parable"},{"time":829000,"text":"sort of got to get working there,"},{"time":831000,"text":"because I'm not prepared to say"},{"time":834000,"text":"that the banana leaf that one eats off of"},{"time":837000,"text":"is the same as the other eats off of."},{"time":842000,"text":"But it is that process that has happened within the man"},{"time":846000,"text":"that changes the banana leaf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"ED: I've been looking forward to sharing that quote with you."},{"time":851000,"text":"Because that's part of where we've got to get to."},{"time":853000,"text":"And I also want to share this one."},{"time":855000,"text":"\"Beyond the age of information is the age of choices.\""},{"time":858000,"text":"And I really think that's where we are."},{"time":860000,"text":"And it's kind of cool for me to be part of a family"},{"time":863000,"text":"and a tradition where he was talking about that in 1978."},{"time":866000,"text":"And part of why this stuff is important"},{"time":869000,"text":"and all the things that we do are important,"},{"time":871000,"text":"is that these are the ideas we need."},{"time":873000,"text":"And I think that this is all part of surrendering to the design journey."},{"time":876000,"text":"That's what we all need to do."},{"time":878000,"text":"Design is not just for designers anymore. It's a process. It's not style."},{"time":881000,"text":"All that great thinking needs to really get about solving"},{"time":884000,"text":"pretty key problems."},{"time":886000,"text":"I really thank you for your time."},{"time":888000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}